(24, 1, 'triguna 50 kg', 'arsktri', '3808', 0, 'Description:\r\n\r\nTrigunaâ¢ can be used to improve poor soils, or to rebuild soils which have been damaged by improper nutrient management. They can make poor soils more usable, and can be used to maintain soils in peak condition. In the integrated nutrient management approach, soil conditioners are integral part of the agronomic package.\r\nBenefits :\r\nCorrects soil pH which could be alkaline or acidic in nature.\r\nImproves the physical and chemical health of soil.\r\nImproves the biological health.\r\nHelps in making nutrients readily available to soild.\r\nAlleviates nutrients toxicities.\r\n', '<table>\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th>Nutrient</th>\r\n			<th>Content</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Calcium</td>\r\n			<td>15%</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Magnesium</td>\r\n			<td>3%</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Sulphur</td>\r\n			<td>5%</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Seaweed</td>\r\n			<td>Q.S.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Crops Recommended :</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Field Crops</td>\r\n			<td>Cotton, Paddy, Wheat, Maize, Mustard, Pulses.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Vegetables</td>\r\n			<td>Okra, Brinjal, Peas, Tomato, Chillies.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Horticulture Crops</td>\r\n			<td>Grapes, Citrus, Mango, Banana</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Dosage</strong>&nbsp;:</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Available Packagings</td>\r\n			<td>50 Kgs</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Recommended per Acre</td>\r\n			<td>200 Kgs.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Time of Application</td>\r\n			<td>15 days before sowing / transplanting.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', 1, '2023-11-16 22:04:43', 1, '2023-11-16 22:05:55', 1, 3, 1),
(25, 1, 'phosrich 50kg', 'arskrich', '3808', 0, 'Phosporous is an essential nutrient for plant health and catalyst in key biochemical reactions. Phosphate Rich Organic Manure (PROM) is a value added product produced by co-composting high-grade rock phosphate in fine size with organic matter collected from various sources such as Farm Yard Manure, Straw of paddy or wheat, Press mud, Compost from Urban waste.\r\n\r\nPhosphate Solubilizing Bacteria (PSB) and nitrogen bacteria are added to improve the efficiency.', '<p>Contains phosphorus in a soluble form. Best source of Phosphate produced by co-composting the high grade rock phosphate.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.gangothrifertilizers.com/products/images/grplant.png\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>PROM is very effective as phosphate fertilizer even in saline soils and also prevents phosphate fixation in soils.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.gangothrifertilizers.com/products/images/uniformcrop.png\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is a complete Eco-friendly product, improves the physical, chemical and biological properties of the soil and increases crop production.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.gangothrifertilizers.com/products/images/microbes.png\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>It improves electrical conductivity of soil and enhances the activity of beneficial micro organisms in soil.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.gangothrifertilizers.com/products/images/ph.png\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Balances the soil pH. It helps in humus formation. Improves the resistance power of crops against various diseases.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.gangothrifertilizers.com/products/images/soilstructure.png\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Essential Macro Nutrient for plant health improves the germination percentage of seeds and helps in effective root development.</p>\r\n', '<p><img src=\"https://www.gangothrifertilizers.com/products/images/phosrich.png\" style=\"width:280px\" /></p>\r\n', 1, '2023-11-16 22:08:28', 1, '2023-11-16 22:09:55', 1, 3, 1),
(26, 1, ' Mulching Film/Mulching Paper 30 Micron 1200mm (Width- 4 Foot) 400 Meter', 'arsk00', '4801', 0, 'MULCHING PROCESS: Mulching is a process of covering soil and forming a protective layer around the plant from natural disaster and unwanted Weeds. Also Mulch Film prevents direct evaporation of soil water which results in better root development.\r\nHIGH QUALITY MULCH FILM : Mipatex black mulch does not allow any kind of light transfer which results in conserving moisture, controlling the unwanted weeds and better crop yield. Our mulch is suitable for almost every crop, reflects 27% off the light to the fruits and plant.\r\nTHICKNESS and QUALITY: We provide you Mulch film ranging from 20 Micron to 20 Micron. Mipatex Mulch film can be used for Vegetable Crop farming.\r\nINSTALLATION: Mark the rows in the field, prepare bedding for crop using manure/compost. Mix the manure thoroughly in the soil. Make sure the bed is flat and remove any kind of previous plants, weed or stones. Then install the mulch film by stretching evenly on the bed. Make a hold with sharp tool and start seeding or planting in the soil through holes.', '', '', 1, '2023-11-17 07:19:57', 1, '2023-11-17 07:22:42', 1, 3, 0),
