se-233x300.png\" style=\"height:300px; width:233px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>STEP 4: In greenhouses, additionally use near vents and doors for better monitoring.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>In taller crops &ndash; hung the sticky traps under the canopy of plant and or 5 ft above the ground level, where the sheet is exposed to light sufficiently.</li>\r\n	<li>Upon contact sticky material can be removed by cooking oil or any mineral oil.</li>\r\n	<li>For plants grown on benches, the sheets may be laid horizontally on the bench.</li>\r\n	<li>Carry out regular checking as and when required for identification of pest variety, counting if necessary, for its abundance and its developmental stages to take corrective pest management actions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>NOTE:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Keep away from children and domestic animals</li>\r\n	<li>Avoid direct contact with skin</li>\r\n	<li>Protective gloves recommended while handling</li>\r\n	<li>Buyer assumes all responsibility for safety and use in accordance with the directions</li>\r\n	<li>If you can spot isolated hot spots early you may need to spray to that small area only.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', 1, '2023-11-18 08:55:00', 1, '2023-12-26 11:07:13', 1, 3, 1),
(42, 15, 'Barrix Hunter â RB Trap and Lure', 'traps', '8424', 0, 'Protect Your coconut, oil palm and date palm Crops from Red Palm Weevil.\r\nOur unique combination of Pheromones and Kairomones effectively attracts and traps these unyielding pests.\r\nEndorsed by the Department of Scientific & Industrial Research and part of the Atal Innovation Mission.\r\nInnovative. Effective. Eco-Friendly.\r\nEasy to installation and use.\r\nTraps Reusable upto 4 Seasons.\r\nSun & Heat Proof.\r\nScientifically Designed Design Patented Product\r\n\r\n\r\nSPECIAL FEATURES OF BARRIX HUNTER TRAP :\r\n\r\nThermo stable, UV Stabilized plastic used and recyclable plastic.\r\nResearch based-pest alluring colour.\r\nEco friendly and user friendly.\r\nSUPERIOR FEATURES OF RPW LURE :\r\n\r\nCellulose Matrix Entrapment Technology.\r\nSynergistic effect with kairomone.\r\n10 times more powerful than ordinary lures.\r\n99% pure isomer specific para pheromone impregnated.\r\nLong lasting performance up to 60 days.\r\nBiodegradable formulation.\r\nNon-toxic & eco-friendly.\r\n\r\nTechnologies used:\r\nIntroducing Barrix Agro Sciencesâ Cutting-Edge Technologies:\r\nCellulose Matrix Entrapment Technology.\r\nSynergistic effect with kairomone.\r\n\r\n?? Ultra Violet Rays Protection Technology: Safeguarding the trap from the degradational effects of UV rays, ensuring optimal performance and durability under the sun. helping the trap for multi seasonal use.\r\n\r\n???? Colour Alluring Technology: Harnessing the power of colors to attract and lure pests, enhancing the efficacy of our trap and maximizing pest capture rates.\r\n\r\n? Rain Protection Technology: Engineered to withstand the harshest weather conditions, ensuring continuous effectiveness even in heavy rain, preventing the degradation of pheromone by rain water.\r\n\r\nExperience the Future of Agriculture with Barrix Agro Sciences â Where Innovation Meets Sustainability.Cellulose Matrix Entrapment Technology.\r\n\r\nSynergistic effect with kairomone.\r\n\r\nDOSAGE:\r\n\r\nFor Identification & Monitoring	1 Trap / acre\r\nNote: If pest trapping is more, then increase the number of traps for mass trapping and control of the pests effectively.\r\n\r\n', '<p>HOW TO FIX BARRIX HUNTER TRAP?<br />\r\nBarrix-Hunter-Installation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Special Note: Trap can be used for many times till the colour of the trap fades.<br />\r\nStep 1: Fix by locking push fit built-in rivets of three wings to the Barrix Hunter Cap.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 2: Fix narrow end of the central axle to three grooves given at the bottom of the wings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 3: Place the central axle in the crescent base bowl.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 4: Now lock the bottom with push fit built-in rivets of wings to the crescent base bowl</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 5: Remove the RPW lure from the pouch and place at the lure placement area.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 6: Fill the crescent base bowl with water till the overflow hole.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 7: Add 5 grams of any detergent / soapnut powder / shampoo to the water and stir.<br />\r\nBarrix-Hunter-RPW-Trap-On-Field-Photos-IPM-tool-Organic-Farming (3)<br />\r\nStep 8: Tie this assembled trap set to the trunk of the tree at 4 &ndash; 5ft above the ground level.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 9: Frequently refill the water into the crescent base bowl.</p>\r\n', '<p>The Red Palm Weevil (RPW) is a highly destructive pest that inflicts significant damage on palm trees. Here are some of the key types of damage caused by the Red Palm Weevil in palm trees:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Boring into Trunk: Adult female RPWs bore into the trunk of palm trees to lay their eggs. They create tunnels, causing structural damage to the tree and weakening its integrity.</li>\r\n	<li>Larval Feeding: The RPW larvae, after hatching, feed voraciously on the inner tissues of the palm tree, including the vascular bundles responsible for nutrient transport. This feeding disrupts the flow of nutrients, leading to reduced growth and overall decline of the tree.</li>\r\n	<li>Stunted Growth: Infested palm trees often exhibit stunted growth due to the damage caused by RPW larvae within the trunk and crown.</li>\r\n	<li>Wilting and Yellowing: As RPW larvae consume the inner tissues, the palm tree&rsquo;s leaves start wilting and turning yellow, leading to reduced photosynthesis and eventual defoliation.</li>\r\n	<li>Frond Damage: The feeding activity of RPW larvae affects the health and vitality of palm fronds, causing them to dry out and collapse prematurely.</li>\r\n	<li>Crown Collapse: In severe infestations, RPW damage can lead to the collapse of the palm tree&rsquo;s crown, resulting in its eventual death.</li>\r\n	<li>Entry of Secondary Pathogens: RPW infestations create entry points for secondary pathogens, such as fungi and bacteria, leading to additional diseases that further weaken the palm tree&rsquo;s health.</li>\r\n	<li>Death of Palm Trees: If left untreated, RPW infestations can cause the death of palm trees, resulting in economic losses for farmers and plantation owners.</li>\r\n	<li>It is essential to implement effective pest management strategies, such as using traps and lures like Barrix Hunter, to control RPW populations and prevent the devastating damage caused by this pest. Early detection and intervention are crucial in protecting palm trees from the destructive impact of the Red Palm Weevil.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 1, '2023-11-18 20:38:00', 1, '2023-12-26 11:03:41', 1, 2, 1),
