icides in addition to many other grasses and broad leaf weeds.</li>\r\n	<li>It is economical because of its broad spectrum activity and low dose.</li>\r\n	<li>No residual effect on succeeding crops</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 1, '2023-12-16 11:30:07', 1, '2024-01-08 13:48:36', 1, 1, 0),
(53, 2, ' Craze', 'craze', '3808', 0, 'DESCRIPTION \r\nCraze (Pretilachlor 50% EC) is a pre-emergence, broad-spectrum herbicide of Chloroacetamide group which controls all type of weeds in rice. Craze absorbed primarily by the germinating shoots, and secondarily by the roots, with trans-location throughout the plant, giving higer concentrations in vegetative parts than in reproductive parts.', '<p><img alt=\"product image 1\" src=\"https://www.dhanuka.com/storage/products/August2021/aA5vwUWBzKrHve350xTI.png\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Craze</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2>DESCRIPTION&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Craze (Pretilachlor 50% EC) is a pre-emergence, broad-spectrum herbicide of Chloroacetamide group which controls all type of weeds in rice. Craze absorbed primarily by the germinating shoots, and secondarily by the roots, with trans-location throughout the plant, giving higer concentrations in vegetative parts than in reproductive parts.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>MODE OF ACTION</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Selective herbicide. It is taken up readily by the hypocotyls, mesocotyls and coleoptiles, and to a lesser extent, by the roots of germinating weeds. Keep 2-3 cm water in the crop and spray uniformly, immediately after transplanting to 4 of days of transplanting or Treat 20-25 kg dry sand with 500 ml of Craze and apply it in the crop immediately after transplanting to within 4 days of transplanting.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>CROPS</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>TARGET PEST/ DISEASE</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>DOSE PER ACRE</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<h3><a href=\"https://www.dhanuka.com/crops/paddy\">Paddy<small><img alt=\"Paddy image\" src=\"https://www.dhanuka.com/storage/crop-targets/July2022/QASv3trOSb40N5c38fLN.png\" /></small></a></h3>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<h3>All narrow and broad leaf weeds- Echinochloa crusgalli, Echinochloa colonum Cyperusdifformis Cyperusiria Fimbristylismilliacea Eclipta alba Ludwigiapulviflora Leptochloachinensis Monochorea vaginalis Panicumrepens</h3>\r\n\r\n		<p>&nbsp;<em>500 ml</em></p>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p>FEATURES &amp; BENEFITS&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Craze is applied before emergence of weeds, within four days of transplanting.</li>\r\n	<li>Craze controls both narrow and broad leaf weeds before the emergence.</li>\r\n	<li>Craze gives control for a longer time.</li>\r\n	<li>Craze is safe to rice crop as compared to other weedicides used in this crop.</li>\r\n	<li>Craze is suitable for integrated weed management.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 1, '2023-12-16 11:35:02', 1, '2024-01-08 13:46:24', 1, 1, 0),
(54, 1, ' Tornado', 'tar', '3808', 0, 'DESCRIPTION \r\nTornado is a broad-spectrum herbicide for post-emergence control of broad leaf & Grassy weeds. It is a systemic herbicide absorbed by the root system and the foliage. It gives longer weed control and is safe for subsequent crop.', '<p><img alt=\"product image 1\" src=\"https://www.dhanuka.com/storage/products/July2022/gxhPmPQ7igr8kfYouFox.png\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Tornado</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2>DESCRIPTION&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Tornado is a broad-spectrum herbicide for post-emergence control of broad leaf &amp; Grassy weeds. It is a systemic herbicide absorbed by the root system and the foliage. It gives longer weed control and is safe for subsequent crop.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>MODE OF ACTION</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Tornado has a dual mode of Action. It is absorbed by the roots and the foliage with translocation with Xylem and Ploem accumulation in the merismetic regions. It distrupts protein and DNA synthesis.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>CROPS</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>TARGET PEST/ DISEASE</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>DOSE PER ACRE</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<h3><a href=\"https://www.dhanuka.com/crops/groundnut\">Groundnut<small><img alt=\"Paddy image\" src=\"https://www.dhanuka.com/storage/crop-targets/July2022/YCpl2RMr9LkCpY9xYXE2.png\" /></small></a></h3>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<h3>Dactyloctenium aegyptium, Digitaria spp., Echinochloa spp., Commelina benghalensis, Digera arvensis, Cyperus difformis</h3>\r\n\r\n		<p>&nbsp;<em>175 ml</em></p>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>PACK SIZE&nbsp;175ml, 500ml, 1 litre</p>\r\n', '<p>FEATURES &amp; BENEFITS&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Unique Chemistry: Tornado has a unique formulation combining two di?erent actives with dual mode of action.</li>\r\n	<li>Fast action: Tornado has quick action on weeds and is very easy to use.</li>\r\n	<li>Rain Fastness: Tornado requires Only 1- 2 hrs of Rain free period for complete absorption into the plant system.</li>\r\n	<li>One Stop solution : Complete solution for control of Grassy &amp; Broadleaf weeds in Groundnut.</li>\r\n	<li>Safe to crop: Tornado does not harm crop of Groundnut at recommended dose.</li>\r\n	<li>Increase Yield: Early control of weeds resulting in higher yield.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 1, '2023-12-16 11:40:43', 1, '2023-12-16 11:52:41', 1, 1, 0),
(55, 2, ' Implode', 'imp', '', 0, 'DESCRIPTION\r\n Implode, Mazie farmers face their greatest challenge in managing weeds, but IMPLODE presents a viable solution by enabling effective control of both narrow leaf and broadleaf weeds within their Maize fields.', '<p><img alt=\"product image 1\" src=\"https://www.dhanuka.com/storage/products/June2023/PW4DtE8ugcUI5HyZVKGL.png\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Implode</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2>DESCRIPTION&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Implode, Mazie farmers face their greatest challenge in managing weeds, but IMPLODE presents a viable solution by enabling effective control of both narrow leaf and broadleaf weeds within their Maize fields.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>MODE OF ACTION</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>IMPLODE, containing the active ingredient Topramezone, is a specialized herbicide designed specifically for Maize cultivation. When applied, IMPLODE efficiently penetrates the roots and shoots of weeds, initiating its action without delay. It disrupts the weed&#39;s ability to extract nutrients from the soil, ultimately leading to comprehensive control from the roots upwards within a span of 10 to 12 days. To enhance its effectiveness against weeds, it is advisable to utilize IMPLODE in conjunction with Dhanuzine and Outright.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>CROPS</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>TARGET PEST/ DISEASE</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>DOSE PER ACRE</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<h3><a href=\"https://www.dhanuka.com/crops/maize\">Maize<small><img alt=\"Paddy image\" src=\"https://www.dhanuka.com/content/images/productDetail/PaddyTableimg1.png\" /></small></a></h3>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<h3>Narrow and Broad Leaf weed</h3>\r\n\r\n		<p>&nbsp;<em>30 ml</em></p>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p>FEATURES &amp; BENEFITS&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Effective Control of Narroe and Broad leaf weeds</li>\r\n	<li>Long Duration of Control</li>\r\n	<li>Safe Crop</li>\r\n	<li>Higher Yield</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 1, '2023-12-16 11:49:20', 1, '2023-12-17 10:54:18', 1, 1, 0),
(56, 14, 'Calaris Xtra ', 'cala', '3808', 0, 'What is Calaris Xtra?\r\nFor Progressive corn growers of India, who are looking for effective control of weeds to help the crop to get right nutrient without competition of weeds. Presenting Calaris Xtra, India\'s first pre-mix: Inspired by nature to deliver better and long duration control of grass and broad leaf weeds.\r\n\r\nWhen and how to use?\r\nRecommended time: apply Calaris Xtra at 3-4 leaf stage of weeds Dose usage: 1400 ml/acre, to be applied with knapsack sprayer with Flood jet or Flat Fan nozzles with 200L of water/acre', '<p><img src=\"https://www.syngenta.co.in/sites/g/files/kgtney376/files/styles/syngenta_cta_half_width/public/media/image/2021/03/19/banner_1.jpeg?itok=kH9nkJwO\" style=\"height:279px; width:550px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>India&#39;s first Pre-mix herbicide</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>India&#39;s first pre-mix post-emergent herbicide for grass &amp; broadleaf weeds...</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.syngenta.co.in/sites/g/files/kgtney376/files/styles/syngenta_cta_half_width/public/media/image/2021/03/19/banner_2.jpeg?itok=vQd5pgIg\" style=\"height:279px; width:550px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Inspired by nature</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>A new age chemistry - inspired by nature, delivers better and long duration control</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.syngenta.co.in/sites/g/files/kgtney376/files/styles/syngenta_cta_half_width/public/media/image/2021/03/19/banner_3.jpeg?itok=4wJQqCZl\" style=\"height:279px; width:550px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Unique combination</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>A unique combination and a dual mode of action - resulting in fast control.</p>\r\n', '<ol>\r\n	<li>CALARIS XTRA</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>Sticky Menu</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Calaris Xtra</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.syngenta.co.in/sites/g/files/kgtney376/files/styles/syn_full_width_scale/public/media/image/2022/06/15/calaris_xtra_web_v2.png?itok=FtAYnhX5\" style=\"height:314px; width:1132px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img sr